  "label": "Vesperglass Lake",
  "description": "Vesperglass Lake occupies a deep basin of rift-scarred stone within Cyrenth Vale, its shorelines ringed by ash-dark scree and low escarpments cut by old faulting. The water remains unnaturally still and dark, reflecting the bruise-hued aurorae as a muted sheen that rarely breaks into natural ripple. Along the margins, abandoned intake pylons and sealed conduit housings project from the rock, their surfaces scoured by atmospheric fallout and long neglect. The surrounding ground bears the flattened traces of former encampments and perimeter works, now reduced to berms and rust-stained earth.",
